        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "SQA Gradation 4 — version-controlled solver with documented regression suite",
        "description": "The CFD solver must be under formal version control, have a documented regression test suite with pass/fail records, and carry a traceable release note for the version used in COU2 simulations. All simulation scripts must be archived with input decks."
      },
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023R2 is used under an FDA-qualified software configuration. Version control records, regression suite results (1 432 tests, 100% pass), and archived input decks are on file. SQA requirement fully satisfied at Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/numerical-code-verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/numerical-code-verification",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification Gradation 4 — order-of-accuracy demonstrated on hemolysis-relevant benchmark",
        "description": "Formal order-of-accuracy study on a benchmark problem representative of high-shear rotating flow must demonstrate convergence at the theoretical rate for both velocity and scalar transport. Results must be published in a peer-reviewed venue or equivalent FDA-accepted validation report."
      },
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy studies are available for canonical pipe and lid-driven cavity flows (Gradation 3), but no peer-reviewed benchmark study demonstrates theoretical convergence for high-shear rotating hemolysis-relevant configurations. The gap between achieved Gradation 3 and required Gradation 4 constitutes a verification shortfall that cannot be waived at MRL 5."
    },
    {
